WEBVTT

00:06.310 --> 00:08.008
♪

00:10.140 --> 00:11.794
[shrieks]

00:17.191 --> 00:18.931
[school bell rings]

00:21.325 --> 00:22.326
[burps]

00:22.370 --> 00:23.066
[tires screech]

00:25.286 --> 00:27.244
D'oh!

00:27.288 --> 00:29.029
[grunts]

00:34.034 --> 00:36.210
Refill!

00:36.253 --> 00:38.255
♪

00:43.130 --> 00:44.261
HOMER:
Kids,

00:44.305 --> 00:45.436
is there anything better

00:45.480 --> 00:48.309
than when a restaurant
misprints a coupon?

00:48.352 --> 00:50.572
-[snaps fingers]
-And with the money we saved,

00:50.615 --> 00:54.228
your mom is getting
a Swedish massage.

00:54.271 --> 00:57.100
[exhales]
All the tension's going

00:57.144 --> 00:58.667
[in Patty's voice]:
out of my body.

00:58.710 --> 01:00.886
[guttural moans]

01:00.930 --> 01:03.454
Now let's take one deep breath
of this classy place

01:03.498 --> 01:05.761
before we go back
to our lousy car.

01:05.804 --> 01:08.242
-[all inhaling]
-[French accent]: Excuse me,

01:08.285 --> 01:10.548
that air is the property
of this restaurant.

01:10.592 --> 01:12.507
Fine, I'll give it back.
[belches loudly]

01:12.550 --> 01:15.249
[laughter]

01:15.292 --> 01:16.728
-Good one.
-[belches]

01:16.772 --> 01:19.688
-[belches]
-Memory book.

01:19.731 --> 01:21.255
Okay, kids.
I admit we hustled

01:21.298 --> 01:23.170
the restaurant there,
but that's it.

01:23.213 --> 01:24.823
I don't want you to think
this is the way

01:24.867 --> 01:26.173
you get ahead in life.

01:26.216 --> 01:29.393
Do not take advantage
of someone else's mistakes.

01:29.437 --> 01:31.743
-Your car, sir.
-But that's not...

01:31.787 --> 01:34.355
[heavenly chorus]

01:34.398 --> 01:35.312
You see that, kids?

01:35.356 --> 01:37.140
It's the kind of car
they don't make anymore.

01:37.184 --> 01:39.708
Windshield that breaks into
a thousand glass razor blades.

01:39.751 --> 01:41.753
Your lap is the cup holder.

01:41.797 --> 01:44.234
Vinyl seats that can
melt your ass.

01:44.278 --> 01:46.193
God, do I want to drive it.

01:46.236 --> 01:49.631
[shudders]:
Oh... so useless.

01:49.674 --> 01:53.243
This is the car
I've always wanted.

01:53.287 --> 01:54.940
You'll never have
a car this nice.

01:54.984 --> 01:56.768
You'll never have
a girlfriend this cute.

01:56.812 --> 01:58.292
That's right!

01:58.335 --> 02:01.164
And you'll never have
exhaust this toxic.

02:01.208 --> 02:02.209
[tires screech]

02:05.081 --> 02:07.344
Oh, I need this.
I've always needed this.

02:07.388 --> 02:09.433
Get in, kids, get in.

02:09.477 --> 02:11.392
Dad, what were you
just telling us?

02:11.435 --> 02:13.002
This is morally wr...

02:13.045 --> 02:15.352
Whee!

02:15.396 --> 02:17.311
Pull every knob.
Press all the buttons.

02:17.354 --> 02:18.573
Find out what things do.

02:20.575 --> 02:22.011
[grunting]

02:25.319 --> 02:26.798
Don't you
"chitty chitty bang bang" me!

02:26.842 --> 02:28.844
-[grunting]
-["Chitty Chitty Bang Bang"
playing]

02:33.457 --> 02:34.806
Ooh, what's this crank for?

02:34.850 --> 02:36.460
Duh, rolling down the window.

02:36.504 --> 02:38.680
Hmm. How do I put on
the air conditioning?

02:38.723 --> 02:40.812
Uh, you're doing it.

02:40.856 --> 02:42.988
Aw, cool. An ashtray.

02:43.032 --> 02:45.339
[gasps]
A full ashtray!

02:45.382 --> 02:48.559
Uh-uh-uh!
Bad, bad, bad!

02:48.603 --> 02:51.214
Ah, smooth.
Bad, bad.

02:51.258 --> 02:52.911
[small car honks]

02:52.955 --> 02:55.349
[honks]

02:55.392 --> 02:59.353
Now, to tie them in a bow.

02:59.396 --> 03:01.224
[grunts]

03:01.268 --> 03:05.054
My husband-- he's doing
something incredibly stupid.

03:06.490 --> 03:08.362
Look at this beautiful color.

03:08.405 --> 03:11.713
Seafoam. This is what
cars used to look like.

03:11.756 --> 03:14.019
And what the sea
used to look like.

03:14.063 --> 03:17.240
-[tires screech]
-LISA AND BART: Whee!

03:17.284 --> 03:18.589
Whoa!

03:18.633 --> 03:21.244
Put this on the list of things
we don't tell your mother.

03:21.288 --> 03:23.420
Including the fact
there is a list.

03:24.508 --> 03:26.510
LISA:
Aw, it's over.

03:26.554 --> 03:28.469
Now, to teach you kids
a life lesson.

03:28.512 --> 03:31.863
Moments of pure joy
always have consequences.

03:31.907 --> 03:33.300
We already knew that.

03:33.343 --> 03:35.171
Yeah. Why do you think we exist?

03:35.215 --> 03:37.347
Quick!
Put on your innocent faces.

03:37.391 --> 03:39.523
Innocenter... innocenter.

03:39.567 --> 03:43.397
Uh, yeah, I'm, uh, I'm sorry,
you gave me the wrong car.

03:43.440 --> 03:47.488
The moment I realized,
I brought it back immediately.

03:47.531 --> 03:49.490
You stole my car.

03:49.533 --> 03:53.842
My precious 1957 Cadillac
Eldorado Biarritz convertible

03:53.885 --> 03:57.411
in the original seafoam,
with the illegal brodie knob.

03:57.454 --> 04:00.631
Oh, God. Tell me right now you
did not touch my brodie knob.

04:00.675 --> 04:02.633
Absolutely not.

04:02.677 --> 04:04.679
This is the brodie knob.

04:04.722 --> 04:06.724
Oh. I was all over thatthing.

04:06.768 --> 04:08.378
You're in big trouble.

04:08.422 --> 04:10.424
They're gonna charge you
with grand theft auto.

04:10.467 --> 04:13.296
A lousy game
but a magnificent law.

04:13.340 --> 04:15.733
Listen, I'm sorry.
Really sorry.

04:15.777 --> 04:18.301
I just wanted to give
my kids a ride,

04:18.345 --> 04:19.955
show them the house
I was born in,

04:19.998 --> 04:21.696
show them the house
I'm gonna die in,

04:21.739 --> 04:22.914
then drive through
a cornfield for kicks.

04:22.958 --> 04:23.959
Whoo-hoo!

04:25.569 --> 04:27.876
I gave you
the USS Enterprise,

04:27.919 --> 04:31.401
and you returned
with the Orville!

04:31.445 --> 04:33.969
I am so sorry.
You're absolutely right.

04:34.012 --> 04:35.362
I'll get it fixed by a pro.

04:35.405 --> 04:37.668
I'll get you a license plate
frame saying

04:37.712 --> 04:40.715
"My other car is a..."
insert dumb movie reference.

04:40.758 --> 04:43.457
Tron Legacy Light-Cycle.
Well, okay.

04:43.500 --> 04:46.938
I suppose I could allow you to--
oh, God!

04:46.982 --> 04:48.592
No!

04:48.636 --> 04:52.814
My mint condition copy
of Radioactive Mannumber one!

04:52.857 --> 04:53.945
[grunts]

04:53.989 --> 04:56.165
This was the comic
I always wanted most

04:56.208 --> 04:58.515
since I was an athletic,
popular child.

04:58.559 --> 05:00.169
Look, you're a nice guy.

05:00.212 --> 05:03.520
When have you ever seen me
be a nice guy?!

05:03.564 --> 05:06.567
I am pressing charges!

05:09.787 --> 05:10.832
Is this yours?

05:10.875 --> 05:13.008
Yes.

05:14.488 --> 05:15.532
Simpson, get on the bike.

05:15.576 --> 05:17.578
Put your arms around me.

05:17.621 --> 05:20.711
Now, head on my shoulder.
Yeah... aw, that's nice.

05:20.755 --> 05:22.583
And don't lean the same way I do

05:22.626 --> 05:23.758
[chuckles]: or we're both dead.

05:23.801 --> 05:25.760
Uh, by the way,
you're under arrest.

05:25.803 --> 05:28.458
Uh, doesn't the law say
I need a helmet, too?

05:28.502 --> 05:30.199
Another law you're breaking.

05:33.637 --> 05:35.596
Why are you riding a motorcycle?

05:35.639 --> 05:37.380
It's not for fun!
I got arrested!

05:37.424 --> 05:39.295
That's worse!

05:40.427 --> 05:42.994
Your Honor, I'm scared.
Okay, I screwed up.

05:43.038 --> 05:46.607
If you'll permit, may I read
a speech in my defense?

05:46.650 --> 05:47.608
Did your daughter write it?

05:47.651 --> 05:49.436
Absolutely not.

05:49.479 --> 05:51.742
Sir, if an opportunity
came along

05:51.786 --> 05:54.223
to give your kids
a memory they'll never forget,

05:54.266 --> 05:56.486
-wouldn't you hop
in the driver's seat?
-[mouthing]

05:56.530 --> 05:58.967
A golden day with their dad.

05:59.010 --> 06:01.535
What could be more innocent?

06:01.578 --> 06:04.494
All I know is that
as that gas gauge read empty,

06:04.538 --> 06:07.671
our hearts were full.
Full of love.

06:07.715 --> 06:13.024
Love of what our country does
best: build cars 60 years ago!

06:13.068 --> 06:14.678
[sniffling]

06:14.722 --> 06:17.551
I'm a judge.
But I'm also a father.

06:17.594 --> 06:19.466
A father whose ex-wife
only lets him see the kids

06:19.509 --> 06:22.512
on summers and Christmas.
I don't need you to rub it in.

06:22.556 --> 06:23.861
I find the defendant guilty.

06:23.905 --> 06:26.647
Your Honor, I'm not the one
on trial here.

06:26.690 --> 06:28.126
Yes, you are.

06:28.170 --> 06:29.563
[all gasping]

06:29.606 --> 06:33.218
"Hire a lawyer," I said.
"Waste of money," he said.

06:33.262 --> 06:37.048
This is what I spend my time
in courtroom audiences for.

06:37.092 --> 06:38.528
This is my Starbucks.

06:43.359 --> 06:44.578
Two weeks.
Two weeks to turn this around.

06:44.621 --> 06:46.101
Lisa, can we get the state

06:46.144 --> 06:48.016
to change its sentencing
guidelines

06:48.059 --> 06:49.321
in the next two weeks?

06:49.365 --> 06:52.455
Ah, the legislative calendar
is pretty full.

06:52.499 --> 06:54.675
And they take off
the second week for Easter.

06:54.718 --> 06:58.069
RomanEaster! To the Byzantine
world, it's nothing!

06:58.113 --> 07:01.551
I'm afraid we have to prepare
for the possibility

07:01.595 --> 07:03.684
that you might go to prison.

07:03.727 --> 07:07.644
ANNOUNCER:
The Arts and Incarceration
Channel presents...

07:10.734 --> 07:13.694
INTERVIEWER:
What advice would you give
to a new inmate?

07:13.737 --> 07:15.478
Everything can be a weapon.

07:15.522 --> 07:18.481
I saw a guy get his eye gouged
with uncooked spaghetti.

07:18.525 --> 07:20.918
You sound
like you've seen a lot.

07:20.962 --> 07:24.531
I've seen things and done things
I ain't proud of.

07:24.574 --> 07:25.488
And I'm the chaplain.

07:25.532 --> 07:27.838
I can't take this, Marge.

07:27.882 --> 07:31.102
Maybe I can make peace
with Comic Book Guy.

07:31.146 --> 07:33.104
Do you think so?
He's an angry man.

07:33.148 --> 07:36.717
His favorite thing is Star Wars,
and he hates Star Wars.

07:36.760 --> 07:38.545
I'll talk to him.

07:38.588 --> 07:41.722
Careful, Marge.
He's a lazy, overweight slob.

07:41.765 --> 07:43.463
Don't fall in love with him.

07:47.771 --> 07:51.514
Comic Book Guy,
my husband is reallysorry.

07:51.558 --> 07:55.344
Okay, he screwed up.
But he doesn't belong in prison.

07:55.387 --> 07:58.086
I beg to differ.
That car is very special to me.

07:58.129 --> 07:59.914
When I was young,
my father took me in it to...

07:59.957 --> 08:02.786
-Buy comic books?
-No, not comic books.

08:02.830 --> 08:05.180
Everything in my life
is not comic books, okay?

08:05.223 --> 08:06.790
We bought baseball cards.

08:06.834 --> 08:09.924
Look, we'll detail your car
and fix your comic book.

08:09.967 --> 08:13.754
This is not about my car.
It is about me getting respect.

08:13.797 --> 08:16.539
I want all the Little Lulus
five dollars can buy.

08:16.583 --> 08:18.672
And make it snappy,
Blobba the Hutt.

08:18.715 --> 08:22.327
Jabba is actually quite slim!
For a Hutt.

08:22.371 --> 08:23.720
Just get the Lulus.

08:23.764 --> 08:26.244
Or I'll take my business
to Build-A-Bear.

08:27.811 --> 08:30.031
Here you go. Five dollars'
worth of Little Lulus.

08:32.033 --> 08:34.818
As for you, I am not budging.

08:34.862 --> 08:37.908
Like the door of Superman's
Fortress of Solitude

08:37.952 --> 08:40.694
when the Beatles tried to visit.
Pure folly.

08:40.737 --> 08:43.000
That comic is noncanonical.

08:43.044 --> 08:46.482
The only thing noncanonical
in my store is Snoopy

08:46.526 --> 08:50.617
dressed as Sgt. Rock
for an ill-timed Vietnam war ad.

08:50.660 --> 08:54.403
I see. Well, I'm sorry
to have bothered you.

08:54.446 --> 08:56.579
Yes, don't let the door hit you
on the way out.

08:56.623 --> 08:58.581
No, seriously.
It's just been painted.

08:58.625 --> 09:01.671
Oh. That's what
being nice gets you.

09:02.890 --> 09:06.850
Mom, Dad, I think I found
the answer on the Internet!

09:06.894 --> 09:09.418
Lisa, nothing good
ever comes from YouTube.

09:09.461 --> 09:12.247
Except ducks eating watermelon.

09:17.034 --> 09:20.516
No, no.
Sentencing mitigation videos.

09:20.560 --> 09:22.518
People have had
their jail terms reduced,

09:22.562 --> 09:24.868
or even gotten off death row

09:24.912 --> 09:27.654
by producing slick
video appeals to the judge.

09:27.697 --> 09:31.832
Finally, a way for rich people
to bend the system their way.

09:31.875 --> 09:33.834
Mr. Burns got off the hook once

09:33.877 --> 09:37.707
by using a video directed
by Guillermo del Toro.

09:37.751 --> 09:41.058
Hello, I am, uh, film director
Guillermo del Toro.

09:41.102 --> 09:45.280
Uh, when I was a young boy,
I fell in love with monsters.

09:45.323 --> 09:48.718
Frankenstein's monster,
King Kong, Son of Kong,

09:48.762 --> 09:51.025
Nosferatu, Godzilla,
Mechagodzilla,

09:51.068 --> 09:52.635
Godzilla's nephew Godzooky,

09:52.679 --> 09:54.506
Mothra the caterpillar,
Mothra the moth,

09:54.550 --> 09:56.291
the Blob fromThe Blob...

09:56.334 --> 09:58.859
and Godzilla's cousin,
Sheldon Godzilla.

09:58.902 --> 10:01.644
Lesser known
but equally horrifying.

10:01.688 --> 10:04.865
Monsters, yes.
But they are capable of love.

10:04.908 --> 10:07.868
Which brings us
to Montgomery Burns.

10:07.911 --> 10:09.304
Oh, hello.

10:09.347 --> 10:10.784
Did someone mention me?

10:10.827 --> 10:13.308
DEL TORO:
From birth, he was not wanted.

10:15.963 --> 10:17.704
Then came the real monsters:

10:17.747 --> 10:20.794
the bullies that hated him
just because he was wealthy.

10:20.837 --> 10:22.839
And maybe he rubbed it in
a little.

10:28.279 --> 10:30.673
But no one knows
the real Mr. Burns.

10:43.338 --> 10:44.948
I love Señor Burns.

10:44.992 --> 10:46.558
Who are you?

10:46.602 --> 10:48.909
He combines the ancient evil
of Cthulhu

10:48.952 --> 10:51.085
with the trim physique
of Slender Man.

10:51.128 --> 10:53.957
Señor Burns demonstrates
that in all so-called monsters

10:54.001 --> 10:56.264
beats a heart.
Thank you for listening.

10:56.307 --> 10:57.700
And thank you,
Georgia Film Commission,

10:57.744 --> 10:59.136
for the 22% discount.

10:59.180 --> 11:01.704
I'll see you wherever
free people congregate.

11:01.748 --> 11:03.488
Like the Yale Club.

11:03.532 --> 11:06.753
[orchestral fanfare]

11:09.320 --> 11:12.497
Wow. Maybe I've been
all wrong about evil.

11:12.541 --> 11:15.718
Once again, Mr. del Toro
stripped away the darkness

11:15.762 --> 11:17.720
and found beauty at its core.

11:17.764 --> 11:19.679
Like that fish-snuggling movie.

11:21.637 --> 11:22.594
Excuse me.

11:22.638 --> 11:24.292
[coughs]

11:24.335 --> 11:27.077
Ah... you told me you've
never been to Missouri.

11:27.121 --> 11:29.732
You're right, honey.
Hollywood can solve anything.

11:29.776 --> 11:32.126
Except its own lack
of creativity and diversity.

11:32.169 --> 11:33.736
Now, how do we make this thing?

11:33.780 --> 11:36.217
I think we should use
a videographer.

11:36.260 --> 11:37.827
There's one left in town.

11:39.829 --> 11:42.310
I will do anything
for your wedding video.

11:42.353 --> 11:46.444
Color, black and white, or
Polaroid Swinger, cha cha cha.

11:46.488 --> 11:48.795
I gotta warn you,
my camera hand is shaky

11:48.838 --> 11:52.015
because I have
a major vitamin E deficiency.

11:52.059 --> 11:55.018
No problemo.
It works fine if you just

11:55.062 --> 11:56.454
nod your head like this...

11:56.498 --> 11:58.500
[warbling]

12:01.851 --> 12:03.766
You know, we could
just do it ourselves.

12:03.810 --> 12:07.944
Yeah. Those are the words
that are killing my profession.

12:08.728 --> 12:10.555
Now you say nice things
about me.

12:10.599 --> 12:12.035
So what is it
you're looking for?

12:12.079 --> 12:14.385
Words or something?
Uh, human words?

12:14.429 --> 12:17.954
Okay, uh, Homer Simpson,
uh, well, real family man.

12:17.998 --> 12:20.261
Yeah. Always brings his kids
into the bar.

12:20.304 --> 12:23.046
Not one of them aristocrats
who gets all bent out of shape

12:23.090 --> 12:24.918
when there's a mouse
in his beer.

12:24.961 --> 12:27.616
Hey, Moe. I need you to file a
serial number off a wheelchair.

12:27.659 --> 12:28.835
HOMER:
Cut!

12:28.878 --> 12:31.228
Hmm... Homer Simpson?
How can I put this?

12:31.272 --> 12:35.145
Ah, we've never had an employee
get rehired so many times.

12:35.189 --> 12:38.366
Homer Simpson has two children
enrolled in our school.

12:38.409 --> 12:40.498
That's all I'm
comfortable saying.

12:41.978 --> 12:43.806
All right, let's see
what you got.

12:43.850 --> 12:46.026
I had to edit a little.

12:47.070 --> 12:49.072
Homer Simpson. Family man.

12:49.116 --> 12:50.944
Happy. Aristocrat.

12:50.987 --> 12:52.380
Too. Cool. Comfortable.

12:52.423 --> 12:54.904
Homer is a...
grace to the family.

12:54.948 --> 12:56.950
He is an ape...le father.

12:56.993 --> 12:59.387
I warned Marge... marry him.

12:59.430 --> 13:02.869
That's the best you can do?
I'm screwed!

13:02.912 --> 13:05.654
Not while Ican use
Final Cut Pro.

13:05.697 --> 13:07.047
We'll start from scratch.

13:07.090 --> 13:10.006
Using the only two things
people still believe in:

13:10.050 --> 13:11.878
babies and dogs.

13:11.921 --> 13:13.053
[Snowball II meows sadly]

13:13.096 --> 13:15.664
Sorry, Snowball,
cats are polarizing.

13:15.707 --> 13:17.884
[meows sympathetically]

13:17.927 --> 13:20.060
[sighs] Please...

13:20.103 --> 13:23.715
just give us something
we can use.

13:28.111 --> 13:29.069
We're ready.

13:29.112 --> 13:31.245
Oh, now the dog
won't cooperate.

13:31.288 --> 13:34.074
There's a trick that always
works with Kevin James.

13:36.946 --> 13:38.469
[panting]

13:41.255 --> 13:43.779
♪ I think I'll color
this man father...♪

13:43.823 --> 13:45.912
MARGE: He's a guy who gets off at 5:00

13:45.955 --> 13:49.089
and comes directly home
to be with his kids.

13:49.132 --> 13:51.656
♪ Said I'm gonna
color him father♪

13:51.700 --> 13:53.267
♪ Color him father...♪

13:53.310 --> 13:56.270
He's incredibly generous
to his friends and neighbors.

13:58.838 --> 14:02.450
In his spare time,
he loves PTA meetings.

14:02.493 --> 14:04.756
Helping with the Cub Scouts.

14:04.800 --> 14:07.237
Or just going to the movies.

14:07.281 --> 14:09.239
This is Maggie, our baby.

14:09.283 --> 14:12.112
And she understands
what's going on.

14:12.155 --> 14:15.332
She's never said a word,
but I get the feeling

14:15.376 --> 14:18.335
she wants to say something now.

14:18.379 --> 14:21.121
Nee... Da... dy.

14:21.164 --> 14:23.819
What a man.

14:25.081 --> 14:27.040
And now we pray.

14:27.083 --> 14:28.737
Bless us, O Lord,
for this bountiful feast...

14:28.780 --> 14:30.130
Not that prayer.

14:30.173 --> 14:32.132
I must say, I am impressed.

14:32.175 --> 14:35.091
So, unless the prosecution has
a rebuttal, I'm inclined to...

14:35.135 --> 14:37.485
Not... so... fast.

14:37.528 --> 14:38.965
Do you have a video, too?

14:39.008 --> 14:40.967
No, that would be pretentious.

14:41.010 --> 14:45.145
-Very well, then.
-I have a speech.

14:45.188 --> 14:48.191
-[somber music playing]
-Comic book sales is
a very fragile field.

14:48.235 --> 14:51.064
Kids hate to read,
the stores smell like farts

14:51.107 --> 14:54.328
-and bubble gum...
-[murmuring in agreement]

14:54.371 --> 14:57.984
Then the things I cherish most--
my father's car,

14:58.027 --> 15:01.117
my precious, precious comic,
and most important,

15:01.161 --> 15:03.815
my dignity-- were taken from me.

15:05.078 --> 15:07.297
I'm just your ordinary
small businessman.

15:07.341 --> 15:10.039
Never took anything from anyone.

15:10.083 --> 15:14.522
But I did dare to think
I would be treated with respect.

15:14.565 --> 15:18.047
I have so many fictional heroes,
Your Honor.

15:18.091 --> 15:21.442
For once, please
give me a real one.

15:23.096 --> 15:25.054
[grunts]

15:25.098 --> 15:27.100
Best. Courtroom speech. Ever.

15:27.143 --> 15:28.101
Yes!

15:28.144 --> 15:30.190
I will render
my sentence tomorrow.

15:30.233 --> 15:32.105
I thank you.
Good night.

15:32.148 --> 15:33.193
Boom.

15:33.236 --> 15:34.977
Wait, wait, wait.
Do you want to go to a movie?

15:35.021 --> 15:36.979
I'll go to a movie
with you, Judge.

15:37.023 --> 15:38.807
-Youwon't be available.
-Oh.

15:44.117 --> 15:45.640
Dad, the computer says...

15:45.683 --> 15:47.990
That computer has brought me
nothing but trouble

15:48.034 --> 15:50.601
and sports scores
while I'm at church!

15:50.645 --> 15:52.473
A store in Ogdenville
just put up

15:52.516 --> 15:55.128
the same Radioactive Mancomic
that we destroyed

15:55.171 --> 15:57.043
in perfect condition.

15:57.086 --> 15:59.001
It's my last hope at freedom.

15:59.045 --> 16:01.917
I mean, how much could
an old comic cost?

16:01.961 --> 16:03.963
[whispering]

16:17.933 --> 16:19.935
[whispering]

16:23.112 --> 16:24.679
-Are you done?
-No.

16:24.722 --> 16:27.638
[whispering]

16:27.682 --> 16:29.075
[tires screech]

16:37.431 --> 16:41.391
You can't be closed.
It's Tuesday at 4:30!

16:41.435 --> 16:46.179
Do you not see the "closed" sign
written in Wakandan?

16:46.222 --> 16:49.182
And I wasted high school
learning German.

16:49.225 --> 16:51.401
Was fur eine Schande!

16:51.445 --> 16:55.492
Well, German is Earth's closest
language to Klingon.

16:55.536 --> 16:56.885
Come on in.

17:16.383 --> 17:17.340
What do youwant?

17:17.384 --> 17:18.950
I'm extremely busy.

17:22.389 --> 17:24.173
Mm-hmm.

17:25.174 --> 17:26.654
I want to talk to you.

17:26.697 --> 17:30.005
I see we have reached the
epilogue of our little drama.

17:30.049 --> 17:34.096
[screams] No, not the epilogue.
Still plot. Still plot!

17:34.140 --> 17:35.793
Look, I know we've had
our differences,

17:35.837 --> 17:37.317
but we can still be friends.

17:37.360 --> 17:40.146
Like when Superman teamed up
with Lex Luthor.

17:40.189 --> 17:43.497
That was an imaginary story
written by Harlan Ellison

17:43.540 --> 17:45.238
because he wanted to get fired.

17:45.281 --> 17:48.937
Well, maybe thiswill
tickle your ponytail.

17:48.980 --> 17:50.286
-[boing]
-[gasps]

17:50.330 --> 17:54.116
The Ogdenville copy!
It lives!

17:54.160 --> 17:55.030
Am I forgiven?

17:55.074 --> 17:56.249
I'm afraid not. No.

17:56.292 --> 17:59.252
I don't have a choice.
The grudge is still inside me.

17:59.295 --> 18:03.212
Which is also the name of
a low-budget Roger Corman movie.

18:03.256 --> 18:04.953
Oh! What does it take?

18:04.996 --> 18:06.998
How to explain
what I am feeling.

18:07.042 --> 18:09.740
Uh...look around.
What do you see?

18:09.784 --> 18:12.134
Uh... a bunch of stuff
that other people threw out?

18:12.178 --> 18:14.136
Like a mirror,
you see everything

18:14.180 --> 18:16.747
but understand nothing.
Get out.

18:16.791 --> 18:19.402
[sighs] Let's go.

18:19.446 --> 18:20.534
Oh, my God! Oh!

18:20.577 --> 18:24.059
Is that a season one Welcome Back, Kotter
key chain?

18:25.191 --> 18:27.062
It is! The proof...

18:27.106 --> 18:29.630
a John Travolta
who is happy to be there!

18:29.673 --> 18:32.154
How did youget this?

18:32.198 --> 18:34.287
[applause on TV]

18:35.462 --> 18:37.203
Did I ever tell you
about my Uncle Max?

18:37.246 --> 18:38.595
He was the halfback
in the family.

18:38.639 --> 18:40.728
If you gave him a sandwich,
you got half back.

18:40.771 --> 18:43.165
[all laughing]

18:43.209 --> 18:44.166
[giggling]

18:44.210 --> 18:45.602
This is for you, son.

18:45.646 --> 18:47.387
Don't say I never
gave you nothing.

18:47.430 --> 18:49.389
Are you gonna give me
anything else?

18:49.432 --> 18:50.390
Nope. One thing.

18:51.782 --> 18:55.003
Homer, when you look
at your precious totem there,

18:55.046 --> 18:56.526
how does it make youfeel?

18:56.570 --> 18:58.441
I never thought of it before.

18:58.485 --> 18:59.399
I touch it all the time.

18:59.442 --> 19:01.662
I feel unhappy
if I don't have it.

19:01.705 --> 19:03.403
Sometimes I dream about it.

19:03.446 --> 19:05.796
[gasps] I think I love it!

19:05.840 --> 19:08.973
Well put. Now understand this.

19:09.017 --> 19:10.453
Dah!

19:10.497 --> 19:13.326
That is how youmade mefeel!

19:13.369 --> 19:15.110
[whooshes]

19:15.154 --> 19:16.329
Now you see.

19:16.372 --> 19:18.418
And you may consider
the charges dropped.

19:18.461 --> 19:21.029
Let us shake hands,
drink rice wine,

19:21.072 --> 19:22.335
and enjoy Swedish Fish candy.

19:22.378 --> 19:24.641
Are you saying I'm off the hook?

19:24.685 --> 19:26.600
Yes.
In fact, you may be surprised,

19:26.643 --> 19:28.602
but you are now my best friend.

19:28.645 --> 19:30.386
So I'm not going to prison?

19:30.430 --> 19:32.780
No, you are going
to Comic-Con with me.

19:32.823 --> 19:34.477
Oh. Hmm.

19:34.521 --> 19:36.218
Let me see, let me see.

19:36.262 --> 19:37.872
Dad, just say yes.

19:39.830 --> 19:41.223
Is prison still an option?

19:41.267 --> 19:44.139
No. Not until you hold down
Harrison Ford

19:44.183 --> 19:46.228
while I clip off
his fingernails.

19:46.272 --> 19:47.273
-Let's get to it.
-[groans]

19:51.668 --> 19:53.670
[snoring]

19:55.890 --> 19:58.458
-What's this?
-Mitigation video.

19:58.501 --> 20:02.897
When I first met Bart, I was
just a nerdy kid with glasses.

20:02.940 --> 20:05.247
But now this
blue-haired butterfly's

20:05.291 --> 20:07.902
ready to emerge from his pupa!

20:07.945 --> 20:10.513
[sighs] Simpson, you think
this is helpingyou?

20:10.557 --> 20:12.385
[Bart laughing]

